The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, October 04, 2003 				 Lightning claims four on Saptami 
 OUR BUREAU																								Oct. 3: Four persons were killed in lightning strikes last evening in separate incidents in Nadia and North 24-Parganas.																								In Nadia, Kartick Mondal, 30, and Dinesh Mondal, 20, both farmers, were struck on way home from their field in Tehatta. 																								A fellow farmer said it was overcast since morning. They were returning home even as streaks of lightning criss-crossed the horizon. I saw them collapse. They were burnt all over. Dinesh and Kartick were declared dead at the local health centre.																								Additional district magistrate R.K. Biswas said their families will get a one-time grant of Rs 20,000 each, food and clothes. 																								In North 24-Parganas, Yasmin Khan, 28, and Monirul Molla, 22, were killed around seven in the evening. Police said they were residents of a village near Deganga. Subdivisional officer of Barasat Debajyoti Bhattacharjee said they are yet to get a report from the police. 
